    class="share-link share-arrow"
    role="button"
    tabindex="0"
    data-share-options="true"
    data-toggle="gn-share-popover"
    data-placement="bottom"
    data-trigger="focus"
    html="true"
    data-popover-content="#gn-share-popover">
    <svg viewBox="0 0 8 8">
        <use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="//gulfnews.com/svg/gn-sprite.svg#share"></use>
    </svg>
</a>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr class="divider" />

</header>
    <div class="article-body" itemprop="articleBody">

        <figure itemprop="associatedMedia image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject" class="article-main-image media-landscape pull-left">
            <picture>
                <source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="https://imagevars.gulfnews.com/2023/04/24/Earth-Day_187b2ffeb9a_large.jpg">
                <source media="(min-width: 750px)" srcset="https://imagevars.gulfnews.com/2023/04/24/Earth-Day_187b2ffeb9a_large.jpg">
                <img src="https://imagevars.gulfnews.com/2023/04/24/Earth-Day_187b2ffeb9a_medium.jpg" alt="Earth Day">
            </picture>
            <figcaption class="image-caption" itemprop="description">
                Earth Day is celebrated on April 22 to raise awareness about environmental issues and to promote sustainability and conservation efforts worldwide
                <span class="image-credit">Image Credit: Gulf News</span>
            </figcaption>
        </figure>


            <div class="story-block">
<p>Earth Day, celebrated annually on April 22, springs from the vibrant environmental movement of the 1960s and 1970s. It was established to enhance awareness of environmental concerns, champion sustainability, and ignite global actions to protect our Earth. The inception of Earth Day was spurred by US Senator Gaylord Nelson of Wisconsin after he witnessed the catastrophic effects of a massive oil spill in Santa Barbara, California, in 1969.</p>            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>Disturbed by the slow federal response and inadequate environmental protections, Nelson sought to harness the energetic student anti-war movements to boost public consciousness about air and water pollution, aiming to catapult environmental issues into the national political spotlight by engaging the public directly.</p>            </div>
                <div id="PA_mid-article"></div>
                <div class="cacher">
            <div class="story-block">
<p>Selecting April 22 for its strategic timing between Spring Break and final exams — a time likely to maximise participation from socially active college students — Senator Nelson’s initiative led to the inaugural Earth Day in 1970. This mobilisation drew 20 million Americans, representing 10% of the US population at the time, to public spaces in protest against centuries of industrial damage that had significantly impacted human health.</p>            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>This groundswell not only raised awareness but also triggered significant political responses, culminating in the creation of the US. Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) and the passage of landmark legislation such as the Clean Air Act, Clean Water Act, and the Endangered Species Act.</p>            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
<h2><a href="https://whatsapp.com/channel/0029Va23xpxEFeXuMgVqck3B">Get exclusive content with Gulf News WhatsApp channel</a></h2>            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>Since its inception, Earth Day has morphed into a global phenomenon, coordinated by the Earth Day Network and involving over 193 countries, with participation from more than a billion people annually, continuously expanding its reach to address pressing environmental challenges like climate change, renewable energy, and sustainable agriculture. This year marks the 55th anniversary of Earth Day, and the official theme is “Planet vs. Plastic.”</p>            </div>
                        <div class='adv '><div id='gulfnews_opinion_article_1' data-gpt='Gulfnews_Article/gulfnews_opinion_article/gulfnews_opinion_article_1' data-atf='0' data-size='[320,50]' data-size-mapping='[ [ [ 1024, 500 ], [ [300,100], [300,250], [710,250], [710,400], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [ 768, 420], [ [300,100], [300,250], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [640, 320], [ [300,250], [300,100], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [0, 0], [ [300,250], [300,100], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ] ]'></div></div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>In recent years, there has been a marked intensification of student and youth environmental activism, particularly in the North, driven by heightened awareness of environmental issues, the accessibility of global networks, and the pressing nature of climate change. This surge in activism is bolstered by solid educational foundations where environmental education is initiated early and sustained through university life, nurturing a generation deeply invested in environmental concerns.</p>            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>The advent of digital technology has further amplified this movement, enabling activists to organise, mobilise, and connect with global audiences at unprecedented speeds. Influential figures like Greta Thunberg have played pivotal roles, sparking global networks of student activism and showcasing the potent impact of youth leadership in environmental advocacy.</p>            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>Moreover, this movement is characterised by robust international collaboration, with groups like the Youth for Climate and Extinction Rebellion Youth spearheading coordinated global efforts. Support from academic institutions enriches this activism, providing essential resources and fostering skills crucial for effective advocacy.</p>            </div>
                        <div class='adv '><div id='gulfnews_opinion_article_2' data-gpt='Gulfnews_Article/gulfnews_opinion_article/gulfnews_opinion_article_2' data-atf='0' data-size='[320,50]' data-size-mapping='[ [ [ 1024, 500 ], [ [300,100], [300,250], [710,250], [710,400], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [ 768, 420], [ [300,100], [300,250], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [640, 320], [ [300,250], [300,100], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [0, 0], [ [300,250], [300,100], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ] ]'></div></div>
            <div class="story-block">
<div class="more-similar-article">
    <h3 class="text-uppercase similar-title">Read more by Prof Ashok Swain </h3>
    <ul>
            <li>
                <a href="/opinion/op-eds/urgent-calls-for-gaza-ceasefire-amplify-as-unsc-resolution-passes-1.101855234">
                Urgent calls for Gaza ceasefire amplify as UNSC resolution passes
                </a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="/opinion/op-eds/immigration-enriches-societies-cultures-and-economies-1.102078141">
                Immigration enriches societies, cultures, and economies
                </a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="/opinion/op-eds/world-courts-ruling-spotlights-gazas-humanitarian-crisis-1.101972122">
                World court’s ruling spotlights Gaza’s humanitarian crisis
                </a>
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="/opinion/op-eds/nicaragua-makes-a-case-against-germany-at-icj-1.102193575">
                Nicaragua makes a case against Germany at ICJ
                </a>
            </li>
    </ul>
</div>
            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
<h3>Environmental degradation</h3>            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>Additionally, young activists are increasingly making their voices heard in legal and political arenas, advocating for stringent environmental policies and holding governments and corporations accountable through legal actions. This dynamic synergy of educational, digital, institutional, and legal supports not only empowers these activists to demand change but also equips them to provide ideas for solutions, pushing the boundaries of what is politically and socially feasible in combating environmental degradation and climate change.</p>            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>Undoubtedly, in the face of severe environmental crises and the looming threat of climate change, environmental education becomes an essential tool for sustainability. It equips individuals with crucial knowledge about natural systems and the profound impact of human activities, thereby enabling them to make informed decisions and advocate for necessary changes.</p>            </div>
                        <div class='adv '><div id='gulfnews_opinion_article_3' data-gpt='Gulfnews_Article/gulfnews_opinion_article/gulfnews_opinion_article_3' data-atf='0' data-size='[320,50]' data-size-mapping='[ [ [ 1024, 500 ], [ [300,100], [300,250], [710,250], [710,400], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [ 768, 420], [ [300,100], [300,250], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [640, 320], [ [300,250], [300,100], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [0, 0], [ [300,250], [300,100], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ] ]'></div></div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>Environmental education also has the power to shift behaviours and attitudes towards more sustainable practices, for instance, influencing individuals to reduce plastic usage and engage in recycling. It fosters a sense of stewardship and prepares future generations to tackle imminent challenges by equipping them with essential critical thinking skills. Furthermore, it supports informed policymaking and community actions, enhancing urban living conditions through the development of green spaces.</p>            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>Addressing the disproportionate impact of environmental crises on vulnerable populations, especially in developing countries, environmental education is critical in ensuring all segments of society understand and can mitigate environmental risks.</p>            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>The need to integrate environmental education comprehensively is pressing, ensuring that as global environmental conditions evolve, so does our approach to addressing these challenges. Thus, standing at a critical crossroads, the imperative to harness education as a force for environmental action is clear, aiming to secure a sustainable future for all.</p>            </div>
                        <div class='adv '><div id='gulfnews_opinion_article_4' data-gpt='Gulfnews_Article/gulfnews_opinion_article/gulfnews_opinion_article_4' data-atf='0' data-size='[320,50]' data-size-mapping='[ [ [ 1024, 500 ], [ [300,100], [300,250], [710,250], [710,400], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [ 768, 420], [ [300,100], [300,250], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [640, 320], [ [300,250], [300,100], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [0, 0], [ [300,250], [300,100], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ] ]'></div></div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>Globally, environmental education varies significantly, influenced by economic, cultural, political, and environmental factors. In developed countries of the North, such as those in the European Union and North America, environmental education is thoroughly integrated into school curricula at various levels, underscored by strong environmental policies and abundant educational resources. This robust framework is continually enhanced by ongoing research and development.</p>            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>In contrast, developing countries in the South face unique challenges where environmental education often competes with basic educational needs like literacy, yet it frequently incorporates community-based approaches that highlight local environmental issues and integrate indigenous knowledge.</p>            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
    <div class="story-block mb-3 pull-left">
        <a href="https://x.com/EarthDay/status/1781431546404049399" data-show-caption="true" data-embed class="social-embed"></a>
    </div>
            </div>
                        <div class='adv '><div id='gulfnews_opinion_article_5' data-gpt='Gulfnews_Article/gulfnews_opinion_article/gulfnews_opinion_article_5' data-atf='0' data-size='[320,50]' data-size-mapping='[ [ [ 1024, 500 ], [ [300,100], [300,250], [710,250], [710,400], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [ 768, 420], [ [300,100], [300,250], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [640, 320], [ [300,250], [300,100], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [0, 0], [ [300,250], [300,100], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ] ]'></div></div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>Despite these disparities, there is an emerging trend towards global collaboration in environmental education, facilitated by international agencies like UNESCO, which promote the sharing of best practices and the development of universal educational resources.</p>            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>This collaboration aims to cultivate a global comprehension of environmental issues that transcend national boundaries, underscoring the universal necessity to equip all citizens with the knowledge, skills, attitudes, and values required to address environmental challenges and promote sustainable development.</p>            </div>
            <div class="story-block">
<p>As environmental concerns escalate worldwide, the exchange of educational strategies and ideas across different regions becomes increasingly vital, aiming to unify efforts in tackling the planet’s most pressing issues. Therefore, on Earth Day, it is crucial to emphasise the importance of environmental education in fostering a sustainable future.</p>            </div>
                        <div class='adv '><div id='gulfnews_opinion_article_6' data-gpt='Gulfnews_Article/gulfnews_opinion_article/gulfnews_opinion_article_6' data-atf='0' data-size='[320,50]' data-size-mapping='[ [ [ 1024, 500 ], [ [300,100], [300,250], [710,250], [710,400], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [ 768, 420], [ [300,100], [300,250], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [640, 320], [ [300,250], [300,100], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ],[ [0, 0], [ [300,250], [300,100], [1,1], [336,280], [200,200], [250,250] ] ] ]'></div></div>
            <div class="story-block">

<div class="story-block pull-left">
